post_text: Girl Power! The S.H.E Club with Traci Robinson
shared_text:
SHE Girls - Soaring to Heights of Excellence
June 27, 2019 at 10:36 AM ¬∑

Hi, my name is Ms.Traci Robinson. I am the Founder/ Director of the S.H.E Girl's Club. We have been shaping and molding the lives of these beautiful young ladies for 3 years now. We look forward to expanding and impacting the lives of more youth with this special and unique program. I thank God for the vision and the will to have created such a wonderful program. I personally would like to thank the superintendent Ms. April Hart for allowing us the space and the opportunity to bring forth such an important program. Each year thus far has preceded our expectations. We are very excited about this upcoming year. I am truly proud and honored to be a Mama Bear to all of my S.H.E Girls.
We are the helping hands that will assist and encourage our girls to Soar to Heights of Excellence!!
Our Motto:
Creating bonds through -Sisterhood, Friendship, & Education
5 Steps to being a S.H.E. Girl:
Leadership
Purpose
Empowerment
Service
Self-awareness

post_text: FB Friends and Fam, this is my charter school! Ha, its where I spend all my time and money. :)) I have been the Director since 2013. I was the former attorney from 2000-2012! We do a lot of good things on a little budget! It‚Äôs an urban education so our families don't get the funding deserved to urban students. Despite or B grade on value-added state scores, we live on a tight budget. But I don't want my students to feel one pinch. They should be exposed to the best of everything education has to offer. Please help me with donations in kind- books, supplies and items or services that the students need and/or would enjoy! We need everything LOL, and a lot of love! Stakeholder and Partnerships welcomed. Oh, did I mention we LOVE TUTORS AND VOLUNTEERS! Come visit me. Come visit us. You are going to love it here!

post_text: Want better homework results? Make sure your child has a quiet, well-lit place to work on homework. Avoid your child doing homework with the television on or in places with other distractions, such as people coming and going.

post_text:
Parents, be sure to help your child with time management.
Write down a set time each day for doing homework. Don't let your children leave homework until just before bedtime. Think about using a weekend morning or afternoon for working on big projects.

post_text: Did you know Omega-3 fatty acids, found in some fish, nuts, and olive oil, are well known for their brain-boosting potential. One study found that eating a combination of omega-3 and omega-6 fatty acids before a test reduced anxiety.

post_text: Want better homework results? Make sure your child has a quiet, well-lit place to work on homework. Avoid your child doing homework with the television on or in places with other distractions, such as people coming and going.
text: Want better homework results? Make sure your child has a quiet, well-lit place to work on homework. Avoid your child doing homework with the television on or in places with other distractions, such as people coming and going.

post_text:
Parents, be sure to help your child with time management.
Write down a set time each day for doing homework. Don't let your children leave homework until just before bedtime. Think about using a weekend morning or afternoon for working on big projects.

post_text: Parent should always be positive about homework. Be sure to tell your child how important school is. The attitude you express about homework will be the attitude your child takes towards learning.
